<paragraph id="2E605604FFCDFF9A07CCFC381140892F" blockId="16.[211,1172,936,1349]" pageId="16" pageNumber="1553">
This species seems to be closest to 
<taxonomicName id="E9DF2D87FFCDFF9A0542FC3910878F8D" authorityName="Deeleman-Reinhold" authorityYear="2001" box="[605,698,975,999]" class="Arachnida" family="Liocranidae" genus="Jacaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="1553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mihun">
<emphasis id="1CAB8A16FFCDFF9A0542FC3910878F8D" box="[605,698,975,999]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="1553">J. mihun</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, because both species have very distinctly enlarged PME; their palps can be distinguished from other members of 
<taxonomicName id="E9DF2D87FFCDFF9A04EFFC191675886C" authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1897" box="[1008,1096,1007,1030]" class="Arachnida" family="Liocranidae" genus="Jacaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="1553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1CAB8A16FFCDFF9A04EFFC191675886C" box="[1008,1096,1007,1030]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="1553">Jacaena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the pear-shaped bulb anteriorly narrowed, and the apex of the short, triangular conductor is pointing apically (
<figureCitation id="B6E44A81FFCDFF9A06A9FBD81073882C" box="[438,590,1070,1094]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="8.[211,278,1428,1450]" captionTargetBox="[213,1170,168,1394]" captionTargetId="figure-5@8.[213,1170,168,1394]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figure 4. Jacaena spp. Male palps, ventral (A, D, G). Ditto, prolateral (B, E, H). Ditto, retrolateral (C, F, I). Jacaena schwendingeri comb. nov., holotype (A–C); J. lunulata sp. nov., paratype (originally misidentified as Sesieutes schwendingeri) (D–F); J. mihun, holotype (G–I)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6517648" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6517648/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="1553">Figures 4G–I</figureCitation>
cf. 5G–I). The male of this species can be separated from that of 
<taxonomicName id="E9DF2D87FFCDFF9A067AFBB913FF880C" authorityName="Deeleman-Reinhold" authorityYear="2001" box="[357,450,1102,1126]" class="Arachnida" family="Liocranidae" genus="Jacaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="1553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mihun">
<emphasis id="1CAB8A16FFCDFF9A067AFBB913FF880C" box="[357,450,1102,1126]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="1553">J. mihun</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the absence of a small, triangular denticle on the dorsal surface of the conductor (
<figureCitation id="B6E44A81FFCDFF9A06C5FB98106088EC" box="[474,605,1134,1158]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="18.[211,278,1446,1468]" captionTargetBox="[213,1170,167,1412]" captionTargetId="figure-5@18.[213,1170,167,1413]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 10. Jacaena mihun, holotype (A–C); J. thakek comb. nov., holotype (D–F). Male palp, ventral (A, D). Ditto, prolateral (B, E). Ditto, retrolateral (C, F)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6517670" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6517670/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="1553">Figure 10A</figureCitation>
cf. 10D). However, we have a private notion that the boundary between these two species is vague and 
<taxonomicName id="E9DF2D87FFCDFF9A042EFB7911AB88CC" authorityName="Dankittipakul &amp; Tavano &amp; Singtripop" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Dankittipakul &amp; Tavano &amp; Singtripop" baseAuthorityYear="2013" box="[817,918,1166,1190]" class="Arachnida" family="Liocranidae" genus="Sesieutes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="1553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thakek" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="1CAB8A16FFCDFF9A042EFB7911AB88CC" box="[817,918,1166,1190]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="1553">J. thakek</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="0798376DFFCDFF9A0482FB78162588CF" box="[925,1048,1166,1190]" pageId="16" pageNumber="1553" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is possibly a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="E9DF2D87FFCDFF9A06DCFB59101C88AC" authorityName="Deeleman-Reinhold" authorityYear="2001" box="[451,545,1198,1222]" class="Arachnida" family="Liocranidae" genus="Jacaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="1553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mihun">
<emphasis id="1CAB8A16FFCDFF9A06DCFB59101C88AC" box="[451,545,1198,1222]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="1553">J. mihun</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Much larger samples would be needed to corroborate these slight differences as species-specific rather than intraspecific variation because more material recently obtained suggests that 
<taxonomicName id="E9DF2D87FFCDFF9A05FBFB18117E896C" authorityName="Deeleman-Reinhold" authorityYear="2001" box="[740,835,1262,1286]" class="Arachnida" family="Liocranidae" genus="Jacaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="1553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mihun">
<emphasis id="1CAB8A16FFCDFF9A05FBFB18117E896C" box="[740,835,1262,1286]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="1553">J. mihun</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has relatively broad distribution covering northern and north-eastern parts of 
<collectingCountry id="56C81694FFCDFF9A041EFAFB1155894F" box="[769,872,1293,1317]" name="Thailand" pageId="16" pageNumber="1553">Thailand</collectingCountry>
(and most likely extending eastwards to 
<collectingCountry id="56C81694FFCDFF9A0678FAD813A2892F" box="[359,415,1326,1349]" name="Laos" pageId="16" pageNumber="1553">Laos</collectingCountry>
where 
<taxonomicName id="E9DF2D87FFCDFF9A06F1FAD8106F892F" authorityName="Dankittipakul &amp; Tavano &amp; Singtripop" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Dankittipakul &amp; Tavano &amp; Singtripop" baseAuthorityYear="2013" box="[494,594,1325,1349]" class="Arachnida" family="Liocranidae" genus="Sesieutes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="1553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thakek" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="1CAB8A16FFCDFF9A06F1FAD8106F892F" box="[494,594,1325,1349]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="1553">J. thakek</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="0798376DFFCDFF9A0546FADB10EE892F" box="[601,723,1325,1349]" pageId="16" pageNumber="1553" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
was collected).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
